info.additionalInfo:
I started with CSharpner's dark theme, & just kept making alterations.
All the intelligent notation is theirs..
I gave it transparency, a bunch of neon glow effects, 
& changed the logo, because the colors would have been off.

There's an animated Fireworks Background in the code as an Easter egg.

Nerd notes!

For the LOGO
I converted a png to base 64 which you can do online. Notice in my image it repeats 3 times, so use mine as a template to place your own where you want it.. The image is in .c-mw-app-main-header

You can use the glow effect the same way you'd use a background-color. It's in several parts like this, but CSS will see this as one color:




    animation: neon 1s ease infinite;
    -moz-animation: neon 1s ease infinite;
    -webkit-animation: neon 1s ease infinite;
}

@keyframes neon {
    70%,
    200% {
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 .5vw #b112a5d4, inset 0 0 3vw #b112a5d4, inset 0 0 0vw #b112a5d4, inset 0 0 0vw #b112a5d4, inset 0 0 .4vw #b112a5d4, inset 0 0 .5vw #b112a5d4;
        color: #b112a5d4;
    }
    50% {
        box-shadow: 0 0 .5vw #b112a5d4, 0 0 3vw #b112a5d4, inset 0 0 0vw #b112a5d4, 0 0 0vw #b112a5d4, 0 0 .2vw #b112a5d4, 0 0 .5vw #b112a5d4;
        color: #b112a5d4;
    }
}

